                <h5>Sustainable</h5>
                <p>For years we have abused the earth’s fossil fuels and natural resources to satisfy our own needs. Mining,
                    whether for diamonds or coal or any other substance, continues to be one of the most harmful activities
                    for our planet. Apart from taking away land that can be used for a multitude of beneficial reasons, the
                    process itself can cause soil erosion, deforestation and extensive ecosystem destruction. Lab-grown
                    diamonds, on the other hand, do not require extensive displacement of land nor do they directly destroy
                    ecosystems. When you decide to pick a lab-grown diamond over a mined one, you’re doing your little bit
                    to help conserve and preserve the planet without compromising on your quality of life. Remember, we need
                    to make changes today to ensure that we have a tomorrow to look forward to.</p>
                    <h5>Ethical</h5>
                    <p>For many years, people were forced to mine for diamonds in war zones to finance civil wars. These
                        diamonds were called blood diamonds. With lab-grown diamonds, you don’t have to worry about blood
                        diamonds at all since the stones are grown in laboratories. This means there’s almost no question of
                        labour being exploited to mine the diamonds or the stones being used for anything other than to decorate
                        pieces of jewellery. When you opt for a lab-grown stone, you get a beautiful piece of jewellery that is
                        completely conflict-free!
